article.headline: New Orleans 69, Middle Tennessee 65
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- T.J. Worley hit three free throws down the stretch to help New Orleans defeat Middle Tennessee State 69-65 on Saturday night. Worley and Kyndall Dykes each scored 19 points to lead the Privateers (9-11, 4-5 Sun Belt Conference). Justin Archie added 11 points, six rebounds and four assists. After trailing 66-60 with less than a minute remaining in the game, Middle Tennessee's Nigel Johnson made a 3-pointer with 16 seconds left. Dykes then committed a turnover, and Desmond Yates' layup with 10 seconds left made the score 66-65. But Middle Tennessee wouldn't score again, and Worley made 3 of 4 free-throw attempts with the game on the line to preserve the victory. The Blue Raiders (12-8, 6-3) were paced by Yates, who finished with 22 points and five rebounds. Demetrius Green chipped in with 11 points.
